"title": "7386: incense",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7386",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An expensive resin from southern Arabia and the fragrant aroma it emits when offered in worship ritual. It is also called frankincense.</p>\n<h2>Regulations governing the offering of incense</h2>\n<h3>The priest was to keep incense burning on the altar daily</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:7-Exod30:9\">EXO 30:7–30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:16\">NUM 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:10\">DEU 33:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:28\">1SA 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:49\">1CH 6:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:29\">1CH 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:9\">LUK 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Only the priests were to burn incense</h3>\n<p>Korah, Dathan and Abiram:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:16-Num16:18\">NUM 16:16–16:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:35\">NUM 16:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:40\">NUM 16:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:46-Num16:47\">NUM 16:46–16:47</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16-2Chr26:19\">2CH 26:16–26:19</a> <em>Uzziah's pride</em></p>\n<h3>Failure to burn incense is disobedience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:7-2Chr29:8\">2CH 29:7–29:8</a></p>\n<h3>The blending of the incense</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:34-Exod30:38\">EXO 30:34–30:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:6\">EXO 25:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:8\">EXO 35:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:28\">EXO 35:28</a></p>\n<h2>Occasions for offering incense</h2>\n<p>At the setting up of the tabernacle:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:38\">EXO 39:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:5\">EXO 40:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:26-Exod40:27\">EXO 40:26–40:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:1-Lev2:2\">LEV 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:15-Lev2:16\">LEV 2:15–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:15\">LEV 6:15</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:11\">LEV 5:11</a> <em>not to accompany a sin offering</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:12\">LEV 16:12</a> <em>on the Day of Atonement</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:7\">LEV 24:7</a> <em>to accompany bread and oil</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:86\">NUM 7:86</a> <em>As part of the offerings at the dedication of the tabernacle, each leader presented a golden incense dish.</em></p>\n<h2>The altar of incense</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:1\">EXO 30:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:27\">EXO 30:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:8\">EXO 31:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:11\">EXO 31:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:15\">EXO 35:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:25-Exod37:29\">EXO 37:25–37:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:18\">1CH 28:18</a></p>\n<h2>Burning incense to foreign gods</h2>\n<h3>Incense offered to other gods will not bring answers to prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:12\">JER 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:23\">JER 44:23</a></p>\n<h3>Israel disobeyed the LORD's commands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:9-Jer7:10\">JER 7:9–7:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:15\">JER 18:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:13\">JER 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:29\">JER 32:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:5\">JER 44:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:18-Ezek16:19\">EZK 16:18–16:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:28\">EZK 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:2\">HOS 11:2</a></p>\n<h3>The practice continued under successive kings</h3>\n<p>In the early days of Solomon's reign:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:3\">1KI 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:8\">1KI 11:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:43\">1KI 22:43</a> <em>Jehoshaphat</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:3\">2KI 12:3</a> <em>Joash</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:4\">2KI 14:4</a> <em>Amaziah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:4\">2KI 15:4</a> <em>Azariah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:35\">2KI 15:35</a> <em>Jotham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:4\">2KI 16:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:4\">2CH 28:4</a> <em>Ahaz</em></p>\n<h3>It provoked God's anger</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:3\">JER 44:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:17\">2KI 22:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:3\">ISA 65:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:16\">JER 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:17\">JER 11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:5\">JER 44:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:8\">JER 44:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:21\">JER 44:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:35\">JER 48:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:13\">HOS 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>The destruction of pagan incense altars</h2>\n<h3>As part of God's punishment for disobedience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:30\">LEV 26:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:4\">EZK 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:6\">EZK 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:13\">EZK 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Their destruction in religious reformations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:4\">2KI 18:4</a> <em>under Hezekiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:5\">2KI 23:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:8\">2KI 23:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:4\">2CH 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:7\">2CH 34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:5\">NEH 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:9\">NEH 13:9</a></p>\n<h3>Their destruction brought God's blessing and deliverance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:9\">ISA 27:9</a></p>\n<h2>The significance of incense</h2>\n<h3>A right heart attitude is more important to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:3\">ISA 66:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:20\">JER 6:20</a></p>\n<h3>It both accompanies and symbolises prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:2\">PSA 141:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:8\">REV 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:3-Rev8:4\">REV 8:3–8:4</a></p>\n<h3>It symbolises worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:4\">2CH 2:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:46\">DAN 2:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:11\">MAL 1:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:11\">MAT 2:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:4\">HEB 9:4</a></p>\n<h3>It brings pleasure</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:9\">PRO 27:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:6\">SNG 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:6\">SNG 4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:41\">EZK 20:41</a></p>",
